Male genitalia (
Fig. 51
). Uncus trapezoidal, wide at base, narrowed to apex, with long setae laterally, apex straight, curved downward in lateral view. Gnathos narrowly tongue-shaped, apex slightly curved downward in lateral view. Tegumen with height 2.3 times length of uncus. Valva wide at base, narrowed toward cucullus; cucullus elongate oval, length 2.5 times of maximum width, straight on dorsal margin, obtuse on ventral margin, rounded at apex; inner process hooked; costa convex triangularly; sacculus 2/3 length of valva, concave at basal 1/3 on ventral margin, with long setae, apex broadly rounded, free from valva, exceeding ventral corner of cucullus. Vinculum narrowly banded; saccus U-shaped, 1/4 length of uncus. Juxta elliptical; anellar lobes conical, twice length of juxta, with long setae. Aedeagus 1.2 times length of valva, with a sclerotized plate near base, basal 2/3 almost uniform, distal 1/3 tapered to apex; distal process half length of aedeagus, slenderly clubbed; cornutus absent.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 71
). Papillae anales longer than wide, fused in conical shape posteriorly, with short setae. Intersegmental membrane between papillae anales and eighth abdominal segment approximately twice length of papillae anales. Apophyses posteriores approximately 1.5 times length of apophyses anteriores. Eighth segment straight on posterior margin, with long setae; eighth tergite straight anteriorly; eighth sternite semi-oval anteriorly. Antrum sub-rectangular, width three times of length, with dense microspines on inner wall. Ductus bursae almost uniform, twice length of corpus bursae. Corpus bursae rounded, rugose; signum slender, crescent, at middle of corpus bursae, length as wide as corpus bursae. Appendix bursae wider and twice longer than corpus bursae, with a few spicules scattered at transition of corpus bursae and appendix bursae; ductus seminalis tubular basally, slender and with dense granules distally.
